data.description:
# Introduction

Dark Forest is an MMO strategy game built with zkSNARKs on Ethereum and xDAI. We had full fun playing Dark Forest, but at the same time, we have some ideas and plans to **improve the game using zero-knowledge proofs and blockchain technology**.



# Our ongoing programs

## 1. DF ARES

In March 2023, we have chosen to hold ”**DF ARES**” — seasonal Dark Forest community rounds to explore more possibilities around the game mechanics of Dark Forest and to test the latest technological innovations. DF ARES 0.1.1 round will be hosted this summer.

DF ARES 0.1.1 game demo:

https://github.com/dfarchon/DF-ARES-basic-demo

more information about DF ARES:

https://www.notion.so/dfares/DF-ARES-Main-ca9238c3fee8418d933079d5d28eab3b

## 2. Game Strategy Evaluation Sandbox 

Game Strategy Evaluation Sandbox: Empowers advanced players to evaluate the excellence of their game strategies in a more quantitative way, including but not limited to fine-grained real-time data analysis, simulated opponent matchups against specific strategies, video replay analysis of past games, and more.

## 3. Dark Forest Plugins 

Game experience optimization, timely release of user-friendly plugins according to the latest game rule changes.

## 4. DF ARTEMIS

We release DF ARTEMIS, which is a Planet-targeted bounty mercenary system.

Funders can publish tasks to planets, mercenaries can attack those planets and get rewards.

questions.query: Have you participated in a previous Gitcoin Grants Round? If so, please name the rounds or link the builder profile associated with previous rounds.
How does your project contribute to the growth of the OSS ecosystem? Please provide specific examples of how your application enhances or expands the current ecosystem.
questions.explanation:
We release new versions of the game every 2-3 months, designing and developing different features based on various game mechanics. For each round, we open source all the code and host a public testing event lasting about a week to attract players and developers.

Since early 2023, we have conducted four rounds of Dark Forest Ares, each with different game mechanics. On average, each round attracts 200+ player accounts. In each round, developers create different plugins based on the unique goals of the game.

questions.query: What features or use cases does your dApp/App present? How is it differentiated?
questions.explanation:
Dark Forest is a space-themed, fully onchain MMORTS game that utilizes zero-knowledge proofs.

Since early 2022, the official team has not released new rounds, so Dark Forest Ares is a community-driven version built upon the open-source code of Dark Forest. Our goal is to continue improving the game’s logic and build an active player community.

Fully onchain games mean that both game data and logic are executed on the blockchain, demonstrating a strong pursuit of decentralization. This represents cutting-edge exploration in the direction of large-scale decentralized applications.

questions.query: What are your plans for further development, and how will the grant funds be used to achieve these goals?
questions.explanation: We will continue to release new game development versions every 2-3 months. The funding will primarily be used for development costs, player rewards during testing events, and operational expenses.
